munity comes together is uplifting. Her stories of what she saved from the fire will resonate with anyone who has lived through a crisis, and help make sense of a life-changing event that garnered interest throughout the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSurvivalzAlbertazFort McMurray. 0aWildfireszAlbertazFort McMurray. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Fire & Emergency Services.2bisacsh  aNatural Disasters / Community / Memoir.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311127268908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2019z978311127498040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978177212471240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781772124712423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781772124712/original  a978-3-11-127268-9  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-127498-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles